<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                1906</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: Supplementing my oral
                            communications on the same subject, I have the honor to inform your
                            excellency that the foreign envoys extraordinary to the forthcoming
                            wedding of His Majesty the King of Spain, my august sovereign, which is
                            to take place during the month of June next, will, during their stay at
                            the court, be the guests of His Majesty’s Government.</p>
                        <p>I am glad to communicate the foregoing to your excellency, and avail
                            myself, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">L. Pastor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>